<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="73">
The only three previously described species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Scherer, 1962" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ulrica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ulrica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ulrica</taxonomicName>
are known from Venezuela. There are about 20 more species that remain undescribed in various collections, but they were also collected from Venezuela. Among West Indian genera, 
<taxonomicName authority="Scherer, 1962" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ulrica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ulrica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ulrica</taxonomicName>
can be recognized based on the following key. The five specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Scherer, 1962" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ulrica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ulrica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ulrica</taxonomicName>
that were collected in Puerto Rico come from the same mountain region, El Yunque. Based on the labels, the substrate that they came from differs for two species: it is moss for 
<taxonomicName authority="Scherer, 1962" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ulrica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ulrica eltoro" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eltoro">Ulrica eltoro</taxonomicName>
and leaf litter for 
<taxonomicName authority="Scherer, 1962" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ulrica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ulrica iviei" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iviei">Ulrica iviei</taxonomicName>
. The exact collecting locations for 
<taxonomicName authority="Scherer, 1962" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ulrica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ulrica iviei" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iviei">Ulrica iviei</taxonomicName>
are unknown.
</paragraph>
